# CustomMetadata RECORDS (AFM_Runbook.*) are deployed by a dedicated, verified
# step — `make sf-seed-runbooks` (scripts/seed_runbook_cmdt.sh) — NOT by the bulk
# `make sf-deploy`. They are excluded here so the bulk force-app deploy/validate
# stays robust; the seed step handles them on every org.
#
# WHY a dedicated step: the afm-dev demo org GACKs on ANY CustomMetadata *record*
# deploy through the Metadata API — `UNKNOWN_EXCEPTION` / internal code
# -315522575, org-wide, ZERO component errors. This is afm-dev/platform-specific,
# NOT a universal Salesforce limit and NOT our records: a brand-new clean CMDT
# type fails identically; SOAP+REST and API 60-66 all fail; the CMDT type+fields
# and all non-CMDT metadata deploy fine; and licensing the org's only managed
# package (`devedapp`) to the deploying user did NOT clear it — so it is platform-
# managed CMDT this org can't resolve, not a subscriber-license issue. Including a
# record in the bulk deploy would therefore fail the whole deploy on afm-dev.
#
# The seed step is org-adaptive: standard Metadata API deploy on a healthy org,
# Apex Metadata API fallback only on that exact GACK, then SOQL-verified. So this
# exclusion can stay even once the GACK is resolved — or be dropped to fold the
# records into the bulk deploy on a known-healthy org. The *.md-meta.xml files
# remain the canonical source. See _private/docs/build/07_agentforce.md (Decisions
# log + support case) and memory afm-dev-cmdt-mdapi-deploy-broken.
**/customMetadata/**

# Agentforce Bot / BotVersion / GenAiPlannerBundle are publish-generated by
# `sf agent publish authoring-bundle` (one set per published version). The
# aiAuthoringBundle/*.agent is the version-controlled source of truth (TARS
# pattern); the generated metadata is a build artifact — excluded so
# `make sf-deploy` / `sf-validate` (which deploy all of force-app) stay clean.
# `sf agent publish` regenerates + activates the agent.
**/bots/**
**/genAiPlannerBundles/**
